        [
          "Ventrue money manager who lost it all in the housing crisis and then was saved by a mysterious benefactor who demanded a blood bond.  You are on the run and hoping to find out more, maybe your sire who came to LA will know or be able to help.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "TS"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You have always been good with numbers and what those numbers actually mean. You were embraced right out of college (under clan orders by a traveling Ventrue arms dealer) and placed in the deep end of global market trading. It took about 20 years for you to start being more than just a voice on the phone to some people. You were ok with that. You knew where your talents were, but advancement came with playing the social game... So you tried. That push really made you blossom, and in a few short years you were the talk of the court. Everyone gave you their money to invest and protect, and in turn you were invited to the best parties. Markets rise and fall, but you were not prepared for the downfall of the housing market. In a matter of 12 weeks, you lost 800 Million dollars of other people's money. They started calling to make sure everything was ok, and you had to lie. You could just not imagine what would happen if they knew. You started paying people's dividends out of your own savings, and when that run out, you borrowed money to pay them. One day you were at the end of your rope: you decided you were going to stay in your office untli the sun rose, and have that be that. then the door opened, and it was a man whose features were indescribable in ways only obfuscate can produce. He made you a deal: all the money, influence, and reputation back. In exchange, you had to become his thrall. At first, you didn't think your stranger could solve your problems, so you agreed just so you could have someone else to blame. But it did work. In three days, all the money was back. Your debts were paid. But now you were enslaved to a stranger. You hit the road, not stopping for more than a week. You finally made it to Los Angeles, where you heard your sire had gone. You don't know each other well, but some friends are better than none."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Marco del Juro",
          "Reference: (If any)",
          "Ventrue Clanbook",
          "",
